&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Care Support Worker – General Adult – NHS Professionals&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust: East Suffolk and North Essex Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations covered: Ipswich &amp; Colchester&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay rates: (please note the rates below do not include holiday pay as this is accrued and paid separately)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Day: £9.21&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Night/Saturday: £13.63&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sunday/Bank Holiday: £17.08&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE:TO APPLY FOR THIS POSITION YOU MUST HOLD A LEVEL 2 OR HIGHER HEALTH &amp; SOCIAL CARE CERTIFICATE AND MUST HAVE ATLEAST 3 MONTHS WORKING EXPERIENCE IN A HOSPITAL/HOSPICE ENVIRONMENT.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals offer the opportunity to work flexibly, without having to comprise on your career, so whether you are looking for full time, part time or flexible hours, NHS Professionals could be the perfect fit. You can even book your shifts in the comfort of your own home!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within East Suffolk &amp; North Essex Foundation Trust for an experienced Care Support Worker, who is looking for a flexible role within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Along with the opportunity to work in a friendly and dynamic team NHS Professionals offer great competitive rates and free training and even the opportunity to work at both Colchester &amp; Ipswich Hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To monitor patients whilst carrying out the activities and identify and report any changes in the patient’s health and wellbeing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all changes relevant to patient care are communicated to the nursing staff, prior to end of shift and documented appropriately in patients’ notes, correctly carry out those aspects of the Care Plan that have been delegated and agreed within the Community Nursing team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate and work together with other teams within Provider Services, and other providers to ensure optimum patient centred care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use equipment to manoeuvre patients as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To respect patient’s dignity, wishes and beliefs, involving them in shared decision, Making and obtaining patient consent for specific activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Post Requirements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful candidate will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have at least 6 months UK experience within a Hospital/Hospice over the last 2 years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to work as part of a team and independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to pass a full DBS check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In return for their hard work the successful candidate will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive competitive rates of pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualify for an annual leave allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to enrol in a pension scheme if they so wish&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to choose their own shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have priority booking of shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive free training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that you will be contacted via email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your both your inbox and junk emails regularly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
